    "narrative": "Our core lineup for April 25th leans heavily on volume and specific platoon advantages, led by **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.12). **Cal Raleigh** is our premier play, benefiting from a soft matchup against Liberatore and a prime spot in the two-hole, while **Geraldo Perdomo**\u2019s leadoff placement and favorable SP skill data make him an elite source of efficient production. We are also capitalizing on the Eury P\u00e9rez matchup; despite his talent, the wind out and his notoriously slow delivery create a \"green light\" environment for our squad. This has elevated the profiles of **Luis Arraez**, **Matt Chapman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Drew Gilbert**, as the combination of high-contact profiles and the potential for stolen bases against a slow delivery outweighs the neutral park factors.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card involved **Jeremiah Jackson** (45.71), who remained on the bench despite his elite park factors against Crochet. The optimizer ultimately prioritized the superior lineup position and platoon stability offered by our starting outfielders over **Jeremiah Jackson**'s high-variance upside against a top-tier arm. Elsewhere, we are cautious with **Daulton Varsho** (46.62) and **Taylor Ward** (59.22); while **Taylor Ward** benefits from a massive park boost, his matchup against Crochet is the highest-risk encounter of the day. We are monitoring all lineups closely for late scratches, but with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** anchoring the utility spot with a reliable 65.06, we remain confident in this high-floor configuration to maintain our momentum in the Roto standings.",
